[normal]&#xa0;[bold]It should be noted that recommendations regarding devolution of local taxation form part of a package of measures aimed at securing financial self-suffici
[normal]ency for the Core Cities which in turn benefits local communities.
[normal] It is import
[normal]ant to bear this in mind when considering the implications of tax revaluations wh
[normal]ich
[normal], taking an approach which does not end up having the perverse and anti-localist outcome of
[normal] reduc
[normal]ing
[normal] Local Authority income and
[normal] thereby
[normal] increas
[normal]ing
[normal] dependency on central Gov
[normal]ernment funding. As such, local taxation must be taken in the round 
[normal]with cities able to devise comprehensive strategies designed
[normal] to address local priorities in line with the overarching aim of financial self-sufficiency.
